description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_config.c
Lines: 379-380

Bandwidth value is decoded as uint32_t but cast to uint16_t without validation:
```c
uint32_t val;
if (!zcbor_uint32_decode(state, &val)) {
    ...
}
config->bw_khz = (uint16_t)val;
```

If CBOR payload contains a bandwidth > 65535, the value silently truncates. Should validate range before assignment.

Impact: Silent data corruption of radio config with malformed CBOR input.

Category: CORRECTNESS - missing input validation
